<!DOCTYPE html>
<html lang="en">
<head>
  <meta charset="UTF-8">
  <meta name="viewport" content="width=device-width, initial-scale=1.0">
  <title>You Learned: Cookies</title>
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/style.css">
  <link rel="stylesheet" href="/css/learn.css">
</head>
<body>
  <div class="learn-page">
    <img src="/images/logo.png" alt="EECS Girls Who Tech Camp" class="learn-logo">

    <div class="learn-hero">
      <div class="hero-icon">🍪</div>
      <h1>Challenge 2 Complete!</h1>
      <p class="hero-subtitle">Cookie Monster</p>
      <div class="flag-badge"><%= flag %></div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-grid">
      <div class="learn-card skill-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔍</div>
        <h2>Skill Unlocked</h2>
        <h3>Cookie Inspection</h3>
        <p>Cookies are small data files websites store in your browser. <code>F12 → Application → Cookies</code> or <code>document.cookie</code> reveals them all.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card world-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🌍</div>
        <h2>Real World</h2>
        <h3>Session Hijacking</h3>
        <p>Attackers steal session cookies to impersonate users. That's why secure cookies use <code>HttpOnly</code> and <code>Secure</code> flags to protect against theft.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card career-card">
        <div class="card-icon">👩‍💻</div>
        <h2>Career Path</h2>
        <h3>Web Security Engineer</h3>
        <p>Every major tech company — Google, Meta, Amazon — employs security engineers who design systems to protect cookies and user sessions.</p>
      </div>

      <div class="learn-card key-card">
        <div class="card-icon">🔑</div>
        <h2>Key Takeaway</h2>
        <h3>Cookies Are Readable</h3>
        <p>Never store passwords or secrets in client-accessible cookies. Use <code>HttpOnly</code> to block JavaScript access, and <code>Secure</code> to require HTTPS.</p>
      </div>
    </div>

    <div class="learn-nav">
      <a href="/" class="nav-btn secondary">← All Challenges</a>
      <% if (hasNext) { %>
      <a href="/challenge/<%= nextNum %>" class="nav-btn primary">Next Challenge →</a>
      <% } %>
    </div>
  </div>
</body>
</html>
